Share with:
Chief Financial Officer Job (Polyester Manufacturing), Tangerang, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Accounting & Finance
Industry:
Manufacturing
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
06 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting on behalf of one of the largest polyester manufacturing and distribution companies in Indonesia. Our respected client is seeking a financial management professional, ideally a registered accountant, for the job of Chief Financial Officer, to be based in Tangerang, Indonesia. Substantial experience with mergers and acquisitions, and/or IPOs, is preferred. The successful candidate will be working closely with the Director of the Company and will ensure that all finance, administrative and development processes are running optimally. This is an excellent opening for a professional executive with a leading company.
Key responsibilities will include:
Develop financial strategies and action plans
Drive strategic financial vision and all corporate finance activities which include leading the company's "IPO program" and scaling the organization for rapid expansion
Oversee the finance, accounting and all administration process and reporting
Assisting CEO in analysing new business development, feasibility studies and liaises with all related parties including financial institutions, principals, to start up the new developed business
Set up and oversee all financial KPI’s of each subsidiary and establish action plans
Dealing with banks or other financial institutions
Oversee the management and coordination of all fiscal reporting activities
Oversee cash flow of all subsidiaries
Establish and developing the right system information to support the business
Requirements:
Bachelor’s degree in economics, finance or accounting from reputable university
CPA (Certified Public Accountant)
Substantial experience with mergers and acquisitions, and/or IPOs
5 years’ experience as head of finance and accounting (senior manager level)
Experience dealing & establishing financial facilities from banks
Financial reporting analysis expert
English fluency
Computer literacy
Good communication and leadership skills
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.